# @NYMXV05P2808A_BEG_WKMIY
VAR_THRXV05P481A أخبرنا محمد بن محمد بن يعقوب النيسابوري في كتابه ثنا محمد بن محمد بن سليمان ثنا جعفر بن عبد الواحد قال قال لي محمد بن إسحاق بن كثير بن يسار حدثتني @TR1_KMIY@ كرامة بنت محمد بن إسحاق بن يسار عن أبيها محمد عن أبيه إسحاق عن جده يسار أنه أتى النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم فمسح رأسه ودعا له بالبركة. @NYMXV05P2808A_END_WKMIY
PageV05P2808
# @COMMENT: The identity of Muḥammad b. Isḥāq b. Kathīr b. Yasār is unknown and he is only listed in conjunction with this passage in the pre-modern corpus. TDSHV69P189B lists a Muḥammad b. Isḥāq b. Kathīr al-Ṣawrī, who apparently gave dictation to Abū al-Ḥasan Khaythumah b. Sulaymān and heard from Mūʾmmal b. Ismāʿīl. The editor of the text states that his name may have been Muḥammad b. Ibrāhīm b. Kathīr. BNTHV09P144F gives this name but does not list a date of death. TDSHV46P301B, however, gives his name as Abū al-Ḥasan Muḥammad b. Ibrāhīm b. Kathīr b. Wafdān al-Ṣawrī, which would seem to eliminate him as the possible source. Khaṭīb al-Baghdādī gives two variations of the name: Muḥammad b. Ibrāhīm b. Kathīr, Abū ʿAbd Allāh al-Ṣayfūrī who lived at the Syria Gate in Baghdād around 273/886 (see KHTGV02P283A) and a Muḥammad b. Ibrāhīm b. Kathīr al-Ṣawrī but gives not biographical details (see KHTGV08P665A). According to KHTGV07P623A, Jaʿfar b. ʿAbd al-Wāḥid’s kunyā was al-Hāshimī and Muḥammad b. Muḥammad b. Sulaymān is listed as al-Bāghandī. JJKXV02P396D states that Jaʿfar b. ʿAbd al-Wāḥid related from Wahb b. Jarīr, the son of the witness Jarīr b. Ḥāzim. He was also appointed Qāḍī of al-Baṣrah (KHRXV01P328B). He was also appointed chief judge of Rāʾy in 240/854 and died in 258/871 (KHTGV08P55A). 


# @THRXV05P481A_BEG_WKMIY
VAR_NYMXV05P2808A روى جعفر بن عبد الواحد قال قال لي محمد بن إسحاق بن كثير بن يسار حدثتني @TR1_KMIY@ كرامة بنت محمد بن إسحاق بن يسار عن أبيها محمد عن أبيه إسحاق عن جده يسار أنه أتى النبي صلى الله عليه وسلم فمسح رأسه ودعا له بالبركة. @THRXV05P481A_END_WKMIY
